{{wikipediapar|Piercing the corporate veil}}
==English==
===Noun===
'''corporate veil'''
# {{law}} {{finance}} The principle of a [[corporation]] being a separate legal [[person]] from its members (ie. [[shareholder]]s).
===Usage notes===
To pierce or lift this veil is (usually for the courts) to "see through" the company and let its members directly be liable for (or benefit from) the company's legal position.